lib/
├── main.dart                  # App entry point (runs `App`)
├── app.dart                   # App widget + theme, routing, top-level providers
├── core/                      # Cross-cutting code
│   ├── constants/             # App-wide constants (keys, route names)
│   ├── enums/                 # Shared enums
│   ├── models/                # Data models (User, Post, Comment, CommentModel)
│   ├── services/              # External services (Supabase client, storage, API adapters)
│   └── utils/                 # Helpers (formatters, validators, image helpers)
├── features/                  # Feature modules (vertical slices)
│   ├── auth/                  # Authentication flows
│   │   ├── data/              # API / Supabase queries (e.g. auth_service.dart)
│   │   ├── presentation/      # Screens & widgets (login/signup)
│   │   └── state/             # Riverpod state (e.g. auth_controller.dart)
│   ├── blogs/                 # Blog listing, detail, creation
│   │   ├── data/
│   │   ├── presentation/
│   │   │   └── widgets/
│   │   └── state/             # Blog controllers/providers
│   ├── profiles/              # User profiles
│   │   ├── data/
│   │   ├── presentation/
│   │   │   └── widgets/
│   │   └── state/
│   └── comments/              # Comment system (article & image comments)
│       ├── data/              # comments_service.dart (fetch/create/update/delete)
│       ├── presentation/      # Comment UI + composable widgets
│       │   └── widgets/
│       └── state/             # comments_controller.dart, comments_state.dart (Riverpod AsyncNotifier)
└── shared/
    ├── theme/                 # Colors, typography, theme definitions
    └── widgets/               # Reusable UI (buttons, cards)

platforms/                     # Platform-specific folders (android/ ios/ web/ windows/ linux/ macos)
test/                          # Unit & widget tests

Notes:
- State management: Riverpod with AsyncNotifier/AsyncNotifierProvider is used across features.
- Services: `core/services` contains Supabase client adapters, storage helpers, and API wrappers.
- Comments feature supports two contexts: article-level and image-level. The controller uses maps keyed by id to store lists for each article or image and keeps the currently-active `articleId` / `imageId` when operating.
- File layout is vertical-by-feature: each feature groups `data`, `presentation`, and `state` to keep concerns localized and easier to test.

Quick references:
- comments controller: `lib/features/comments/state/comments_controller.dart`
- comments service: `lib/features/comments/data/comments_service.dart`
- auth service: `lib/features/auth/data/auth_service.dart`
